          "1": {
            "Title": "Response Time Improves with Load",
            "Insight": "For endpoint Homepage, response time decreased dramatically as [requests per second](#ClientMetrics) increased, indicating possible initial server cold start optimization.",
            "Details": "[Requests per second](#ClientMetrics) rose from 1.0 RPS at 8:42 AM UTC **to 6.0 RPS by 8:42 AM UTC**, then plateaued between 5.4 and 5.8 RPS until 8:44 AM UTC. [Response time](#ClientMetrics) dropped sharply from **23210ms at 8:42 AM UTC to 2430ms by 8:42 AM UTC**, then fluctuated between 1880ms and 2770ms during the sustained load.",
            "Recommendation": "Consider investigating server startup or warm-up behavior for this endpoint. Review application initialization routines, caching strategies, and ensure readiness before ramping up load."
          },
          "2": {
            "Title": "Latency Remains High Under Load",
            "Insight": "Despite higher [requests per second](#ClientMetrics), the response time for Homepage stabilizes at a relatively high level, suggesting potential backend inefficiency under sustained throughput.",
            "Details": "[Response time](#ClientMetrics) fluctuated between **1880ms and 2770ms** from 8:42 AM UTC to 8:44 AM UTC while [requests per second](#ClientMetrics) maintained a plateau around 5.4–5.8 RPS. No server metrics were provided.",
            "Recommendation": "May review backend processing, optimize heavy computations, or profile database interactions. Consider instrumenting server-side metrics for deeper diagnosis."
          },
          "3": {
            "Summary": "Load test (2 min, 563 VUs) completed with performance degradation. Client-side response times fluctuated heavily with peaks above 23s, suggesting slow responses and possible backend constraints."
          }
        },
        "version": 1,
